---
/**
 * context-engineering/0003 · Figure 4 — "Overlap & the fragmentation failure"
 * (no overlap → fact split vs overlap → fact survives). Copied VERBATIM from the
 * source lesson (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote <sup>). References the
 * shared arrowhead markers (#arwR, #arwG) defined once in Fig1.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Without overlap a fact spanning a boundary is split across two chunks and retrieved by neither; with overlap it survives whole in one chunk."
    >
        <text x="160" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >No overlap &rarr; fact split</text
        >
        <rect x="40" y="30" width="110" height="64" rx="7" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <rect x="170" y="30" width="110" height="64" rx="7" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="95" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110"
            >"The retry limit</text
        >
        <text x="95" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">is set …"</text>
        <text x="225" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">"… to 5 per</text>
        <text x="225" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">minute."</text>
        <line x1="160" y1="20" x2="160" y2="100" stroke="#9a2417" stroke-dasharray="3 3"></line>
        <text x="160" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >neither chunk answers "what is the retry limit?"</text
        >
        <line x1="160" y1="128" x2="160" y2="150" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <text x="160" y="170" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >retrieval misses the fact</text
        >

        <text x="480" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Overlap &rarr; fact survives</text
        >
        <rect x="360" y="30" width="130" height="64" rx="7" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <rect
            x="470"
            y="30"
            width="130"
            height="64"
            rx="7"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            opacity="0.55"></rect>
        <text x="425" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.2" fill="#111110"
            >"…retry limit is</text
        >
        <text x="425" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.2" fill="#111110"
            >set to 5 / min"</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >shared boundary text keeps the fact whole in chunk 1</text
        >
        <line x1="480" y1="128" x2="480" y2="150" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <text x="480" y="170" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >retrieval finds it</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        <b>Context fragmentation:</b> a single fact split across a boundary lives whole in neither chunk,
        so no chunk is a complete answer and retrieval misses it. Overlap shares boundary text so the
        fact survives intact in at least one chunk.<sup><a href="#s5" id="r5b">5</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
